OL,3,CDad of IPP Prisoner: 'how long do they
OL,4,Cwant to keep him... until he's in a
OL,5,Cbox?'
OL,7,FOn Friday 24 May 2024, the Victims and
OL,8,FPrisoners Bill was given Royal Assent,
OL,9,Fbut the Labour Party failed to back an
OL,10,Famendment tabled by the Tory peer,
OL,11,FLord Moylan, which campaigners said
OL,12,Fwould have changed the parole process
OL,13,Fto potentially enable more IPP
OL,14,Fprisoners to be released.
OL,16,FUnder the amendment, the Parole Board
OL,17,Fwould have had to prove that an IPP
OL,18,Foffender was too dangerous to be
OL,19,Freleased, rather than the prisoner
OL,20,Fhaving to prove they were no risk to
OL,21,Fthe public.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/7
