OL,3,CDad of IPP Prisoner: 'how long do they
OL,4,Cwant to keep him... until he's in a
OL,5,Cbox?'
OL,7,FA Labour spokesperson told ITV News:
OL,8,F"It is right that IPP sentences were
OL,9,Fabolished and we supported the
OL,10,Fgovernment's decision to bring forward
OL,11,Fa statutory action plan in the recent
OL,12,FVictims and Prisoners Bill.
OL,14,F"Public protection is at the centre of
OL,15,Four approach. It is not possible to
OL,16,Fmake assessments on the individual
OL,17,Fneeds of IPP offenders from Opposition
OL,18,Fwithout the relevant information,
OL,19,Fwhich is confidential.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/7
